docs.abstract: The guilty verdict against Guy Wesley Reffitt came as prosecutors expanded their investigation into the Capitol attack by indicting a former leader of the far-right group the Proud Boys.
docs.snippet: The guilty verdict against Guy Wesley Reffitt came as prosecutors expanded their investigation into the Capitol attack by indicting a former leader of the far-right group the Proud Boys.
docs.lead_paragraph: A federal jury on Tuesday swiftly convicted the first accused Jan. 6 rioter to go on trial even as prosecutors announced they had expanded their inquiry by indicting a former leader of the Proud Boys, the far-right nationalist group that played a prominent role in the Capitol attack.

headline.main: Texas Man Convicted in First Jan. 6 Trial
headline.print_headline: First Jan. 6 Trial Ends in Texas Man’s Conviction

docs.abstract: A show at the Metropolitan Museum, organized around a single marble sculpture, re-examines works of art representing slavery and abolition.
docs.snippet: A show at the Metropolitan Museum, organized around a single marble sculpture, re-examines works of art representing slavery and abolition.
docs.lead_paragraph: Traditional museums are literally conservative places. They’re built to freeze objects in time, to shield them from change. Too often the conservative impulse extends to institutional thinking, which leaves cultural ideals and values embodied in objects embalmed in Beauty and Greatness, and left at that.

headline.main: ‘Carpeaux Recast’: A Sculptural Gem With a Knotty Back Story
headline.print_headline: A Lesson In Slavery, Enshrined In Marble

docs.abstract: Many Indigenous Australians had seen the case as a test of whether the authorities could be held accountable after what they call decades of abuses.
docs.snippet: Many Indigenous Australians had seen the case as a test of whether the authorities could be held accountable after what they call decades of abuses.
docs.lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia — A police officer in Australia was found not guilty on Friday in the death of a 19-year-old Indigenous man whose shooting more than two years ago prompted widespread protests and worsened long-simmering tensions over the government’s treatment of the country’s native peoples.

headline.main: Australian Police Officer Acquitted in Death of Indigenous Teenager
